1
00:02:42,890 --> 00:02:44,980
Did the Marines win?

2
00:02:44,980 --> 00:02:46,210
They did, didn't they?

3
00:02:46,210 --> 00:02:48,260
Oh, it's getting clearer now.

4
00:02:48,260 --> 00:02:50,750
Have the Whitebeard Pirates lost?

5
00:02:50,750 --> 00:02:52,820
Did the Marines really pull through?

6
00:02:53,660 --> 00:02:56,020
The war at Marineford between
the Whitebeard Pirates and Marine Headquarters

7
00:02:56,020 --> 00:02:59,430
The war at Marineford between
the Whitebeard Pirates and Marine Headquarters

8
00:02:59,430 --> 00:03:04,690
took longer than anticipated
due to the enemy's tenacity.

9
00:03:04,690 --> 00:03:08,430
However, at the end of an arduous fight
in the name of justice,

10
00:03:08,430 --> 00:03:13,460
our Marines have prevailed over
the Whitebeard Pirates and their accomplices.

11
00:03:13,460 --> 00:03:19,310
We are happy to report that Marine
Headquarters has achieved total victory!

12
00:03:20,950 --> 00:03:22,380
They did it!

13
00:03:25,650 --> 00:03:30,020
The Marines are invincible!
Here's to our heroes!

14
00:03:35,430 --> 00:03:40,100
I can't wait for the day I get
reassigned to Headquarters!

15
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:46,150
The war is over!

16
00:03:46,150 --> 00:03:47,730
Hooray!

17
00:03:47,730 --> 00:03:49,370
Thank goodness!

18
00:03:49,370 --> 00:03:53,510
The legendary pirate Whitebeard
has been vanquished!

19
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:59,520
The war is over, right?

20
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:01,850
Yes, we're safe now!

21
00:04:01,850 --> 00:04:03,360
This is great!

22
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:04,580
They did it!

23
00:04:04,580 --> 00:04:05,990
We're safe!

24
00:04:05,990 --> 00:04:09,230
Hooray for the Marines!
Hooray for the World Government!

25
00:04:09,230 --> 00:04:14,220
And for victory, justice and peace:
Hip! Hip! Hooray!

26
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:17,670
– Hip! Hip! Hooray!
– Hip! Hip! Hooray!

27
00:04:24,490 --> 00:04:31,080
Seven ships lurk in the waters
near the battlefield that was Marineford.

28
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:34,250
Key players of the new pirate era...

29
00:04:34,250 --> 00:04:38,630
have gathered to witness
this historic turning point.

30
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:42,290
Staring at the dust of battle
rising above Marineford—

31
00:04:42,290 --> 00:04:45,870
evidence of the workings
of justice in the Great Pirate Era—

32
00:04:45,870 --> 00:04:50,240
they sense the unrest of the changing times.

33
00:04:50,570 --> 00:04:51,900
Captain Drake...

34
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:55,340
Finally... it's over.

35
00:04:55,340 --> 00:04:58,540
This will force the Marines to change too.

36
00:04:59,610 --> 00:05:01,750
Soon enough...

37
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:07,690
Whitebeard's territory will sink,
sucked down in a whirlpool of blood.

38
00:05:09,060 --> 00:05:10,980
Blackbeard is the key.

39
00:05:10,980 --> 00:05:15,530
He gained new followers
and Whitebeard's power.

40
00:05:15,530 --> 00:05:19,800
I am certain they will be
the eye of the typhoon for a while!

41
00:05:23,660 --> 00:05:27,570
Everything... It's all his fault!

42
00:05:27,570 --> 00:05:30,040
I'll track him down soon enough!

43
00:05:30,460 --> 00:05:32,610
Let's go to the New World!

44
00:05:34,580 --> 00:05:37,140
What the hell is going on?

45
00:05:37,140 --> 00:05:39,820
What are you talking about, Apoo?

46
00:05:39,820 --> 00:05:44,700
Those guys are bound to become enemies.
Is he really gonna save him?

47
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:45,650
Huh?

48
00:05:45,650 --> 00:05:50,600
I'm talking about Trafalgar Law.
He's known for his brutality.

49
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:56,740
He wouldn't save Straw Hat Luffy
without some ulterior motive.

50
00:05:59,530 --> 00:06:01,340
How odd.

51
00:06:01,340 --> 00:06:04,620
What seems to be the matter,
Captain Hawkins?

52
00:06:04,620 --> 00:06:09,210
No matter how often I query
the odds of Straw Hat Luffy's survival,

53
00:06:09,210 --> 00:06:11,730
they don't reach zero.

54
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:17,870
To be honest, I was scared
when the war started,

55
00:06:17,870 --> 00:06:20,360
but now the great pirate Whitebeard is dead.

56
00:06:20,990 --> 00:06:23,360
So it's really over, isn't it?

57
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:25,000
Yeah, it is.

58
00:06:31,650 --> 00:06:34,080
What do you mean, "over"?!

59
00:06:34,870 --> 00:06:42,280
That Blackbeard sure is something!
This war cemented him as a major power.

60
00:06:44,850 --> 00:06:48,150
The New World is controlled
by the Four Emperors:

61
00:06:49,250 --> 00:06:53,790
Whitebeard, Red Hair, Kaido, and Big Mom.

62
00:06:53,790 --> 00:06:55,670
But with one of them dead,

63
00:06:55,670 --> 00:06:59,730
the world's off-balance,
and no one can tell what'll happen next!

64
00:06:59,730 --> 00:07:05,000
This is the beginning of a new era
the likes of which no one has ever seen!

65
00:07:16,020 --> 00:07:19,440
The news of the Marine victory
in the battle of Marineford,

66
00:07:19,440 --> 00:07:22,720
the biggest conflict since
the dawn of the Great Pirate Era,

67
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:25,770
spread around the world in the blink of an eye,

68
00:07:25,770 --> 00:07:28,630
and people everywhere rejoiced.

69
00:07:28,630 --> 00:07:30,250
The East Blue...

70
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:31,630
Hooray!

71
00:07:31,630 --> 00:07:33,840
Whitebeard is dead!

72
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:35,630
Yeah!

73
00:07:35,630 --> 00:07:36,910
We're safe now!

74
00:07:36,910 --> 00:07:39,240
I'm so glad!

75
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:41,020
The West Blue...

76
00:07:41,910 --> 00:07:44,930
The sea will finally be at peace!

77
00:07:44,930 --> 00:07:46,610
Hooray!

78
00:07:47,050 --> 00:07:48,090
The South Blue...

79
00:07:48,090 --> 00:07:49,250
Big sale today!

80
00:07:49,820 --> 00:07:51,640
Same here!

81
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:53,350
The Marines have won!

82
00:07:53,350 --> 00:07:55,090
I'm so relieved!

83
00:07:55,090 --> 00:07:58,360
The North Blue...

84
00:07:58,360 --> 00:08:00,960
Yes! I'm so happy!

85
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:03,170
Let's drink, everybody!

86
00:08:03,170 --> 00:08:04,990
There's plenty to go around!

87
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:06,780
The Grand Line...

88
00:08:06,780 --> 00:08:08,730
What should we do tomorrow?

89
00:08:08,730 --> 00:08:10,080
I wanna play tag!

90
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:11,580
Hide and seek!

91
00:08:11,580 --> 00:08:13,270
– Alright!
– Yay!

92
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:18,740
Oh God, we are ever so grateful!

93
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:25,430
As is common when making history,
some facts are left behind as information travels,

94
00:08:25,430 --> 00:08:30,140
and the words "Marine victory"
run ahead of all the rest.

95
00:08:30,140 --> 00:08:35,020
The people, in their excitement over
the news, failed to notice something...

96
00:08:36,730 --> 00:08:37,320
What the...?!

97
00:08:41,670 --> 00:08:44,100
Look at you fools! What a joke!

98
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:49,740
Whitebeard said that the great
treasure One Piece is real!

99
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:52,400
I'm gonna find it!

100
00:08:55,980 --> 00:09:00,020
There's so much more out there! Let's set sail!

101
00:09:05,340 --> 00:09:13,130
A Marine victory... The result alone
does not guarantee peace.

102
00:09:17,980 --> 00:09:21,770
D-Don't come any closer!
Stay out of our town!

103
00:09:23,580 --> 00:09:27,560
With Whitebeard no longer present
to serve as a deterrent,

104
00:09:27,560 --> 00:09:32,330
the seas have become far more precarious.

105
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:40,460
Don't worry. I turned all the Marines to stone.

106
00:09:40,460 --> 00:09:43,600
So, how is Luffy doing?

107
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:45,560
Is it bad? He'll recover, won't he?

108
00:09:47,070 --> 00:09:50,210
How did you know where we'd surface?

109
00:09:50,210 --> 00:09:54,340
I was terrified that the Marines
were still chasing us.

110
00:09:54,340 --> 00:09:56,880
I had Salome follow you underwater.

111
00:09:57,810 --> 00:09:58,380
I see!

112
00:09:58,380 --> 00:10:02,070
Don't change the subject, you fuzzy beast!

113
00:10:02,070 --> 00:10:03,120
I'm sorry!

114
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:04,120
– What a pushover!
– What a pushover!

115
00:10:04,980 --> 00:10:06,720
Ah, Captain!

116
00:10:08,650 --> 00:10:10,720
I did everything I could.

117
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:13,420
You mean... he's okay?

118
00:10:13,420 --> 00:10:19,260
We were able to stabilize him. However...

119
00:10:19,260 --> 00:10:22,870
he suffered unthinkable amounts of damage.

120
00:10:22,870 --> 00:10:25,070
I still can't guarantee that he'll survive.

121
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:31,050
Vhaat did you expect?!

122
00:10:31,050 --> 00:10:32,250
Who said that?!

123
00:10:32,250 --> 00:10:37,650
Even back at Impel Down,
Straw-boy could not even stand!

124
00:10:37,650 --> 00:10:40,290
Straw Hat put his life on the line!

125
00:10:40,290 --> 00:10:42,620
We only managed to escape because of him!

126
00:10:42,620 --> 00:10:47,260
Thanks to Straw Hat, our dream of going to
the Kamabakka Kingdom will become a reality!

127
00:10:47,260 --> 00:10:48,430
Let's set a course!

128
00:10:48,430 --> 00:10:52,070
From Newkama Land
to the heart of Newkamadom!

129
00:10:55,610 --> 00:10:57,140
Who the hell are they?

130
00:10:57,140 --> 00:10:59,940
They were prisoners in Impel Down.

131
00:10:59,940 --> 00:11:01,940
It seems that Luffy befriended them.

132
00:11:01,940 --> 00:11:03,980
They stowed away on the ship.

133
00:11:03,980 --> 00:11:05,140
Yes!

134
00:11:05,140 --> 00:11:09,260
His unrelenting resolve is astonishing!

135
00:11:09,260 --> 00:11:13,080
That is how much he vaanted
to save his brother Ace!

136
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:17,720
That's right! We all saw
how far he pushed himself!

137
00:11:18,390 --> 00:11:22,650
But his brother died... right before his eyes...

138
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:24,500
all to protect him.

139
00:11:27,670 --> 00:11:32,570
There is no justice in this voorld!
It is no surprise that he broke down!

140
00:11:32,570 --> 00:11:36,070
Damn it all! Hang in there, Straw Hat!

141
00:11:36,070 --> 00:11:39,240
You've gotta live! You've gotta, Straw Hat!

142
00:11:45,450 --> 00:11:47,950
What a tragedy!

143
00:11:47,950 --> 00:11:51,890
I wish that I could take his place!

144
00:11:51,890 --> 00:11:54,890
My poor Luffy!

145
00:11:57,550 --> 00:11:58,460
I'm jealous...

146
00:11:58,460 --> 00:12:01,730
Must be nice having the Pirate Empress
care for you that much.

147
00:12:02,870 --> 00:12:05,840
By the vayy, are you
friends viith Straw-boy?

148
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:08,810
No... and I had no obligation to save him.

149
00:12:08,810 --> 00:12:12,510
If you're wondering what motivated me,
I can make up a reason.

150
00:12:12,510 --> 00:12:16,620
No, it is qviite all right.
Sometimes people act on instinct.

151
00:12:16,620 --> 00:12:19,330
Hey, wait! You can't walk around yet!

152
00:12:19,330 --> 00:12:23,510
Don't push yourself like that!
He told you to rest!

153
00:12:23,510 --> 00:12:25,000
Your wound could reopen!

154
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,290
Wh-Where are you going?!

155
00:12:32,050 --> 00:12:33,000
Jinbe!

156
00:12:35,430 --> 00:12:39,200
You're Trafalgar Law from
the North Blue, aren't you?

157
00:12:42,010 --> 00:12:46,250
Sveetheart, is it okay for you
to move around in your condition?

158
00:12:46,910 --> 00:12:48,930
Thank you!

159
00:12:49,940 --> 00:12:51,620
You saved my life!

160
00:12:51,620 --> 00:12:53,890
You need best rest. You could die.

161
00:12:55,150 --> 00:12:58,030
My mind can't find rest. It's hopeless!

162
00:12:58,030 --> 00:13:02,520
What I just lost was too important to me!

163
00:13:02,520 --> 00:13:07,430
That's why I know Luffy
is experiencing far worse!

164
00:13:07,430 --> 00:13:13,700
It was a mercy his survival instincts
forced him to lose consciousness back there!

165
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:16,460
Even if he pulls through,

166
00:13:16,460 --> 00:13:20,680
I can't stop worrying about
the moment he wakes up.

167
00:13:27,510 --> 00:13:28,750
You! Fuzzy beast!

168
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:30,690
Do you have a transponder snail?

169
00:13:30,700 --> 00:13:31,690
What?

170
00:13:31,690 --> 00:13:34,850
Yeah... I mean... Yes, ma'am!

171
00:13:34,850 --> 00:13:36,030
I'm sorry!

172
00:13:36,030 --> 00:13:39,330
I'm jealous... He's like her servant.

173
00:13:40,890 --> 00:13:45,970
I can have the Kuja Pirates' ship take
this submarine across the Calm Belt.

174
00:13:45,970 --> 00:13:50,470
If the government finds out that
Luffy's alive, they will come after him!

175
00:13:50,470 --> 00:13:52,840
I'll give you shelter on the Isle of Women.

176
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:53,550
What?!

177
00:13:53,550 --> 00:13:54,580
Vhaat?!

178
00:13:55,810 --> 00:14:00,760
As long as I am one of the Warlords,
Luffy can rest safely!

179
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:23,350
Fleet Admiral Sengoku!

180
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:26,580
I've been looking for you!

181
00:14:27,540 --> 00:14:29,980
We received word from Impel Down!

182
00:14:29,980 --> 00:14:32,400
Is Magellan all right?

183
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:34,950
He was beaten to within an inch of his life.

184
00:14:34,950 --> 00:14:38,700
As we speak, the medical team
has him in intensive care.

185
00:14:38,700 --> 00:14:43,530
He's a dutiful man; it seems
he's taking full responsibility.

186
00:14:43,530 --> 00:14:47,290
They're saying that if he could
move about, he would end his life.

187
00:14:47,290 --> 00:14:50,100
Don't let him do something so stupid!

188
00:14:50,710 --> 00:14:52,910
Y-Yes, sir!

189
00:14:53,880 --> 00:14:56,640
What is the status of the prison?

190
00:14:56,640 --> 00:14:58,970
Allow me to fill you in.

191
00:14:58,970 --> 00:15:03,480
The situation on Level 6 is especially bad.
It's a complete disaster down there.

192
00:15:05,180 --> 00:15:06,840
A disaster?

193
00:15:13,150 --> 00:15:15,180
What's up, fellas?

194
00:15:15,180 --> 00:15:19,600
Prisoners like you are doomed
to wallow away behind bars forever!

195
00:15:20,530 --> 00:15:24,470
You're all waiting for death's
sweet embrace, so how about this?!

196
00:15:24,470 --> 00:15:28,340
Why don't you all fight
to the death in your cells?!

197
00:15:29,730 --> 00:15:35,480
I'll free the survivors...
and have them join my crew!

198
00:15:35,480 --> 00:15:36,710
Really?!

199
00:15:36,710 --> 00:15:38,220
Get me out of here!

200
00:15:38,220 --> 00:15:40,320
I'll win a spot on your crew!

201
00:15:49,270 --> 00:15:55,470
So he picked the world's most
notorious inmates and freed them?!

202
00:15:55,470 --> 00:15:58,710
Yes... but only four prisoners were taken.

203
00:15:58,710 --> 00:16:03,970
Sanjuan Wolf, Avalo Pizarro,
Vasco Shot, and Catarina Devon.

204
00:16:03,970 --> 00:16:09,920
But there are clearly other
prisoners missing from Level 6!

205
00:16:09,920 --> 00:16:11,480
Which means...

206
00:16:19,490 --> 00:16:25,300
I understand. This means
there are more Level 6 escapees!

207
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:30,940
If even one of the prisoners from Level 6
sneaks into a country somewhere,

208
00:16:30,940 --> 00:16:34,270
its citizens will be in grave danger!

209
00:16:34,270 --> 00:16:37,690
Find out how many there were.

210
00:16:37,690 --> 00:16:41,980
Get their names and put together
a most wanted list immediately!

211
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:44,050
What's wrong?

212
00:16:44,620 --> 00:16:47,350
Well, I... that is...

213
00:16:47,350 --> 00:16:51,560
The World Government has ordered
that this incident on Level 6...

214
00:16:51,560 --> 00:16:53,100
be covered up!

215
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:53,630
What?

216
00:16:53,630 --> 00:16:58,430
Any more blunders on our part will
harm the government's reputation.

217
00:17:03,070 --> 00:17:05,410
Damn them!

218
00:17:32,180 --> 00:17:34,720
You bastard...!

219
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:36,770
Doflamingo!

220
00:17:37,980 --> 00:17:43,410
Moria, you've grown weak, which means
you just aren't Warlord material anymore.

221
00:17:44,710 --> 00:17:51,720
"Died in the Summit War" has a much better
ring to it than "Put down by the government."

222
00:17:52,520 --> 00:17:56,090
Whose idea was this?! Sengoku's?!

223
00:17:56,090 --> 00:18:00,120
No... Even higher than that.

224
00:18:22,450 --> 00:18:28,060
Pirates are nearing Lascamp in the West Blue,
but the bases there have no ships for a counteroffensive!

225
00:18:28,060 --> 00:18:29,550
Codes for the nearest bases?!

226
00:18:30,090 --> 00:18:32,960
The 80th Branch will send reinforcements!

227
00:18:35,430 --> 00:18:38,460
South Blue checking in. Site confirmed!

228
00:18:38,460 --> 00:18:39,500
Dammit!

229
00:18:39,500 --> 00:18:46,070
I thought pirates would be afraid of us after we
killed Whitebeard and won the battle at Marineford!

230
00:18:46,070 --> 00:18:50,140
Instead of laying low,
they're going wild everywhere!

231
00:18:50,140 --> 00:18:52,400
What's gotten into them?

232
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:55,210
Pirates have landed at Lascamp!

233
00:18:55,210 --> 00:18:57,860
We have lost communications. Send backup!

234
00:18:57,860 --> 00:19:00,280
I repeat, send backup to Lascamp!

235
00:19:02,420 --> 00:19:07,230
Load the supplies!
Let's head for the Grand Line!

236
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:15,230
Two weeks after the Summit War,

237
00:19:15,230 --> 00:19:19,340
people around the world
begin to feel its impact.

238
00:19:23,510 --> 00:19:27,450
D-Don't come any closer!
Stay out of our town!

239
00:19:30,720 --> 00:19:33,850
You heard the news, didn't you?

240
00:19:37,760 --> 00:19:42,360
Then you know that this island is
no longer Whitebeard's territory.

241
00:19:42,360 --> 00:19:44,860
This symbol don't mean nothin' anymore!

242
00:19:46,260 --> 00:19:49,670
That's right! Whitebeard's dead!

243
00:20:06,750 --> 00:20:11,020
Listen up and burn this into your memory!

244
00:20:11,020 --> 00:20:13,930
Starting today, this island belongs to me,

245
00:20:13,930 --> 00:20:17,830
the great pirate Brownbeard!

246
00:20:20,870 --> 00:20:25,340
The war ended with Whitebeard's death
and a Marine victory.

247
00:20:25,340 --> 00:20:28,070
But contrary to what the Marines expected,

248
00:20:28,070 --> 00:20:33,440
seas across the globe now show
signs of falling into disarray.

249
00:20:34,550 --> 00:20:36,450
A little while earlier,

250
00:20:36,450 --> 00:20:42,550
Hancock, Jinbe, and their allies decided to harbor
the unconscious Luffy on the Isle of Women.

251
00:20:42,550 --> 00:20:45,990
And now they have
rendezvoused with the Kujus' ship.

252
00:20:47,960 --> 00:20:49,290
Vell then...

253
00:20:49,290 --> 00:20:53,770
my role in supporting Straw-boy is over.

254
00:20:53,770 --> 00:20:55,770
Heehaw!

255
00:20:55,770 --> 00:20:59,270
Can I leave the rest up to you, Jinbe?

256
00:20:59,270 --> 00:21:02,370
Yes. I can't swim yet anyway.

257
00:21:02,370 --> 00:21:06,410
The least I can do is stay here
until Luffy gets well.

258
00:21:07,020 --> 00:21:10,780
I don't know how I can help him, though.

259
00:21:11,750 --> 00:21:14,650
Vhaat a curious tvisst of fate to have met you.

260
00:21:14,650 --> 00:21:15,950
I agree.

261
00:21:15,950 --> 00:21:21,030
We were both locked up in the greatest
prison in the world, Impel Down,

262
00:21:21,230 --> 00:21:24,000
but if it weren't for Luffy,

263
00:21:24,100 --> 00:21:28,600
I suppose we would have
never met each other.

264
00:21:28,700 --> 00:21:35,410
Vee both tried really hard to keep up
viith Straw-boy at Marineford, didn't vee?

265
00:21:35,410 --> 00:21:37,840
It is hard to say goodbye to you,

266
00:21:37,840 --> 00:21:43,080
but boy do I have some sveet candies
vayyting for me to return to my kingdom.

267
00:21:43,080 --> 00:21:46,280
Please take good care of Straw-boy!

268
00:21:51,260 --> 00:21:54,560
Bye, Straw Hat! Thank you for letting us out!

269
00:21:54,560 --> 00:21:58,400
My dream can come true because of you!

270
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:00,800
Say "hi" to him when he wakes up!

271
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:04,270
See you again if we have the chance!

272
00:22:04,270 --> 00:22:05,470
Hang in there!

273
00:22:05,470 --> 00:22:08,440
You can't die, Straw Hat!

274
00:22:08,440 --> 00:22:10,980
Okay, off and avayy!

275
00:22:10,980 --> 00:22:15,480
To the heart of Newkamadom
and the place we have longed to see!

276
00:22:15,480 --> 00:22:16,250
To...

277
00:22:16,250 --> 00:22:18,520
the Kamabakka Kingdom!

278
00:22:18,520 --> 00:22:19,480
Heehaw...!

279
00:22:19,480 --> 00:22:23,820
We need to start heading
for the Isle of Women.

280
00:22:25,260 --> 00:22:26,660
Two weeks have passed.

281
00:22:27,430 --> 00:22:33,600
Law and his crew are staying
just off the coast to treat Luffy.

282
00:22:43,840 --> 00:22:45,040
Wait up!

283
00:22:46,640 --> 00:22:47,750
This is dangerous!

284
00:22:47,750 --> 00:22:49,850
Calm down, Straw Hat!

285
00:22:49,850 --> 00:22:52,520
What will happen if we leave him be?

286
00:22:53,180 --> 00:22:56,020
Well... it's simple.

287
00:22:56,020 --> 00:23:01,890
Like I said when we reached this island,
if his wound opens up, he'll die.

288
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:07,400
Yes! Now's our chance!

289
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:09,270
Let me go, dammit!

290
00:23:09,270 --> 00:23:10,740
Stay still, Straw Hat!

291
00:23:11,020 --> 00:23:12,380
I said let me go!

292
00:23:14,940 --> 00:23:17,380
Where's Ace?!

293
00:23:17,380 --> 00:23:22,080
Ace!

294
00:23:19,040 --> 00:23:22,080
Damn! He's out of control!

295
00:23:22,080 --> 00:23:23,380
Luffy...

296
00:23:23,380 --> 00:23:25,720
We need to inform the Snake Princess!

297
00:23:25,720 --> 00:23:30,390
Snake Princess! Snake Princess!

298
00:23:30,390 --> 00:23:32,760
Luffy has awakened!

299
00:23:32,760 --> 00:23:33,990
– Master Luffy...?!
– Master Luffy...?!

300
00:23:33,990 --> 00:23:35,890
Is this true?!

301
00:23:35,890 --> 00:23:38,360
I'm glad. I wish to see him right away!

302
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:40,200
Nyo, you can't, Snake Princess!

303
00:23:40,200 --> 00:23:43,170
Everybody wants to see Luffy.

304
00:23:43,170 --> 00:23:47,370
Your orders will mean nyothing
if you allow yourself to go and see him.

305
00:23:47,950 --> 00:23:50,610
Men are nyot to set foot on this island!

306
00:23:50,610 --> 00:23:55,280
We are allowing strange men
to stay by the coast;

307
00:23:55,280 --> 00:23:58,850
we cannyot make any more exceptions!

308
00:23:58,850 --> 00:24:00,850
I know, but...

309
00:24:00,850 --> 00:24:03,320
You need to eat something first, Big Sis.

310
00:24:03,320 --> 00:24:08,490
She's right, dear sister! You've barely
eaten a thing since you got back!

311
00:24:08,490 --> 00:24:11,730
That's right! Luffy must be starving too!

312
00:24:11,730 --> 00:24:15,100
Prepare a mountain of our
best dishes to restore his energy!

313
00:24:15,100 --> 00:24:16,930
– Yes, we'd be happy to!
– Yes, we'd be happy to!

314
00:24:16,930 --> 00:24:18,210
I'll assist you!

315
00:24:18,670 --> 00:24:21,170
Let's get to it, ladies!

316
00:24:21,170 --> 00:24:23,440
– Yes, Snake Princess!
– Yes, Snake Princess!

317
00:24:23,440 --> 00:24:28,180
I should nyot press her further.
She just wants to make some food.

318
00:24:28,180 --> 00:24:29,810
And once they're done...

319
00:24:29,810 --> 00:24:33,050
I will personally take them to him!

320
00:24:31,380 --> 00:24:33,050
So you are going?!

321
00:24:33,050 --> 00:24:38,860
We agreed that when he gets well,
we would welcome only Luffy.

322
00:24:38,860 --> 00:24:40,420
Wait for that moment!

323
00:24:40,420 --> 00:24:44,230
I can't! I'm an empress!
You can't tell me what to do!

324
00:24:44,230 --> 00:24:48,730
I said nyo! Nyothing should
supersede our nyational traditions!

325
00:24:49,430 --> 00:24:53,970
Honestly! She's been infected
by such a strong virus!

326
00:24:53,970 --> 00:24:58,110
I cannyot believe that the dread
Pirate Empress has become lovesick!

327
00:24:59,040 --> 00:25:03,080
However... he must have
been like a tiny ant...

328
00:25:03,080 --> 00:25:06,650
diving into a tempest at Impel Down
and Marine Headquarters.

329
00:25:06,650 --> 00:25:11,620
It can only be divine intervention that
allowed him to live and brought him back here.

330
00:25:11,620 --> 00:25:16,760
I wonder what the heavens expect from him.

331
00:25:18,030 --> 00:25:19,860
Hey, pass me the wrench.

332
00:25:19,860 --> 00:25:21,570
Okay, here you go.

333
00:25:21,570 --> 00:25:24,500
Hey! Do you think you can fix the ship?!

334
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:26,000
Yeah, I'll manage.

335
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:28,740
That aside, where did Straw Hat go?

336
00:25:28,740 --> 00:25:30,340
Jinbe is gone too.

337
00:25:30,340 --> 00:25:33,210
I couldn't tell you.

338
00:25:34,010 --> 00:25:39,620
Anyway, I heard that if a man enters
the Isle of Women, he'll get turned to stone.

339
00:25:39,620 --> 00:25:41,690
But maybe it's worth dying for.

340
00:25:41,690 --> 00:25:47,120
According to Aphelandra, only a handful
of the women were there at the port.

341
00:25:47,120 --> 00:25:52,060
An island full of women. It's like a dream!
I wish I could take a look inside!

342
00:25:52,060 --> 00:25:54,200
You'd die, you idiot.

343
00:25:54,200 --> 00:25:56,270
I wonder if there are female bears...

344
00:25:56,270 --> 00:25:57,500
– It's the Isle of Women!
– It's the Isle of Women!

345
00:25:58,070 --> 00:25:59,340
I'm sorry.

346
00:25:59,340 --> 00:26:01,810
Only humans! There are only humans!

347
00:26:01,810 --> 00:26:04,020
I'm really sorry!

348
00:26:40,440 --> 00:26:43,310
Where am I?

349
00:26:44,550 --> 00:26:48,090
Maybe... it was all a dream.

350
00:27:02,840 --> 00:27:06,480
I'm sorry... Luffy...

351
00:27:10,470 --> 00:27:13,780
There was just no saving me.

352
00:27:23,950 --> 00:27:27,360
Go away! Go away!

353
00:27:27,360 --> 00:27:28,630
Luffy!

354
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:32,700
Stop!

355
00:27:39,100 --> 00:27:43,810
Go away! Go away!

356
00:28:21,650 --> 00:28:25,180
If I don't get out of this alive...

357
00:28:25,580 --> 00:28:29,950
could I ask you to look after my brother?

358
00:28:32,420 --> 00:28:35,290
The war is over!

359
00:28:35,290 --> 00:28:36,730
Ace is no longer–

360
00:28:36,730 --> 00:28:39,800
Don't say it! Don't say anything!

361
00:28:41,070 --> 00:28:43,130
I already pinched myself...

362
00:28:43,130 --> 00:28:45,370
hard enough to break the skin!

363
00:28:48,340 --> 00:28:50,770
If this was a dream, I'd be awake by now!

364
00:28:53,180 --> 00:28:55,880
It's not a dream, is it?

365
00:29:04,420 --> 00:29:08,590
Ace is really dead, isn't he?!

366
00:29:15,270 --> 00:29:18,140
Yes, he is dead!

367
00:29:26,010 --> 00:29:29,350
Hey Grandpa, who's this "Ace"?

368
00:29:29,350 --> 00:29:32,550
Oh, he's...

369
00:29:32,820 --> 00:29:36,920
gonna be your big brother!

370
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:42,830
Luffy! I'll see you at
the top of the pirate world!

371
00:29:42,830 --> 00:29:46,230
Come, meet me at the summit!

372
00:30:00,980 --> 00:30:05,420
Ace!

